Some have even suggested that people in the commissioner's office have been winking at one another while they make public pronouncements against steroid use. Commissioner Bud Selig and Major League Baseball have taken a lot of heat over the last several months for their supposed failure to grapple forthrightly with the sport's steroid problem. But as baseball became more aware of this as a growing issue, the commissioner's office did, in fact, act. Indeed, it was probably around 10 years ago that some people in baseball became aware that anabolic steroids were being used by some players. 